An 8-year-old child has drowned at a resort pool in Port Edward, on the south coast of KwaZulu-Natal on Saturday afternoon. Craig Botha of the Kwazulu Private Ambulance Services said the child was found floating at a pool. NSRI Port Edward had started CPR on the child. "Advanced Life Support Paramedics took over resuscitation of the child and were able to successfully get the child's heart beating again. The child was rushed to a local hospital with advanced life support intervention. Despite all the efforts of paramedics and hospital staff, the child deteriorated and was pronounced dead at the hospital. Botha said according to witnesses the child was swimming but he could not confirm if the child had been swimming under the parents' supervision. "Paramedics performed CPR and was to the the hospital but unfortunately deteriorated and was pronounced dead at the hospital," said Botha.